<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900507-0117</DOCNO><DOCID>900507-0117.</DOCID><HL>   Perpetual Financial Corp.</HL><DATE>05/07/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   PFCP</CO><LP>   VIENNA, Va. -- Perpetual Financial Corp. said it expectsto report a pretax charge of as much as $50 million for itsfiscal second quarter to reflect an additional provision toits loan-loss reserve and a write-down of foreclosed realestate.   In the year-earlier quarter, the thrift holding concernearned $5 million, or 30 cents a share. The company said itexpects to report results for the latest second quarter,which ended last Monday, on May 17.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>